Subject: Initialize QtWebEngine before QApplication
Upstream: No (custom patch for Wolfi/Debian packaging)
Origin: https://salsa.debian.org/mendezr/stremio
Author: Juan Manuel MÃ©ndez Rey <vejeta@gmail.com>

This patch ensures QtWebEngine::initialize() is called before creating
the QApplication instance. This is a CRITICAL requirement for Qt WebEngine
to function properly.

According to Qt documentation, QtWebEngine::initialize() must be called
before QApplication is instantiated to properly set up the Chromium
rendering engine.

Reference: https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qtwebengine-overview.html#initializing-qt-webengine

---
--- a/main.cpp
+++ b/main.cpp
@@ -1,5 +1,6 @@
 #include <QApplication>
 #include <QQmlApplicationEngine>
+#include <QtWebEngine>
 #include "mainapplication.h"

 int main(int argc, char **argv)
@@ -3,6 +4,9 @@
 {
+    // CRITICAL: QtWebEngine::initialize() MUST be called before QApplication
+    QtWebEngine::initialize();
+
     qputenv("QTWEBENGINE_CHROMIUM_FLAGS", "--autoplay-policy=no-user-gesture-required");

     MainApp app(argc, argv, true);
